Review: Didn’t even let me fall asleep
Leo and Bob have the most punchable faces in this
The coming of age themes and the sociopolitical (historical) allegory work but as a fantasy it’s not even remotely a world I fantasize about venturing into so loses some of that Miyazaki magic
Not that good if you ask me
We came to suffer mostly and occasionally experience a little togetherness: the movie
Every girl every age all at once
